.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "MAY 2026" "Holberton School" "Unix Command Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- Custom basic UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple command-line interface written in C that interprets and executes standard commands entered by the user. It supports running programs via full system paths, searching through directories listed in the PATH environment variable, and handling specialized built-ins.
.SH FEATURES
.IP \(bu 2
Displays a dedicated command prompt ($ ) and implements dynamic waiting buffers when active interactively.
.IP \(bu 2
Operates cleanly when piped directly through standard non-interactive descriptors.
.IP \(bu 2
Maintains absolute exit state telemetry (e.g., status 127 upon missing targets).
.SH BUILT-INS
.TP
.B exit
Terminates the shell session and cleans up resources.
.TP
.B env
Outputs all active strings present in the current environment context.
.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1), execve(2), fork(2), wait(2)
